conglomerate (0.7.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Danish translation (Michael Rasmussen)

  * Dutch translation (Mark Van den Borre)

  * Improvements to core architecture (Dave Malcolm)
        - Most important structs are now GObjects
        - MVC framework now uses GObjects signals
        - MVC framework allows updates to be amortized,
	  allowed a big optimisation of the "View Source" feature.

  * Complete rewrite of the main editor control: (Dave Malcolm)
        - Fixes numerous bugs
        - In theory, now supports all possible XML
        - Should be more maintainable than old implementation
        - Support for plugin rendering of tags:
	  initial support for various types of list tag and for paragraphs.
        - Various usability fixes:
	  typing now works a lot more like a regular word-processor.

  * Better support for namespaces (Dave Malcolm)

  * Complete rewrite of clipboard, fixing various bugs (Dave Malcolm)

  * Online help, integrated with Scrollkeeper/Yelp (Jeff Martin)

  * Reimplementation of tree views,
  with big optimisations to the change-notification handling. (Dave Malcolm)

  * Adjacent text nodes get merged where necessary. (Dave Malcolm)

  * Stylesheets are now located using the XML catalog (Varga Robert)

  * Improvements to automatic generation of display specs (Jeff Martin)

  * Support for the Kernel Cousin newsletter format (Dave Malcolm)

  * Various bug-fixes (Dave Malcolm)

  * Debian package into "unstable" (closes: #197049 )

 -- Geert Stappers <stappers@stappers.nl>  Fri, 29 Aug 2003 21:04:53 +0200

