conglomerate (0.5.0-0.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * http://people.debian.org/~calvin/unofficial/ says
  """The Debian package version number is parsed from the top entry of
  debian/changelog, eg. mypackage (1.1-0.1)
  unstable; urgency=low. The `-0.1' is the debian internal number, and it must
  be lower than `-1' for unofficial packages.
  Subsequent releases must have `-0.2', `-0.3', etc. An official package will
  have `1.1-1'."""
  It is not in the Debian policy, but it sounds reasonable.

 -- Geert Stappers <Geert.Stappers@xs4all.nl>  Wed, 14 May 2003 20:53:19 +0200

